learning to avoid engaging like this as much as possible is, imo, absolutely critical for people interested in having any chance at building anything that allows for any hope at all in the face of the conditions we are in especially if any of that building happens online 5/

it doesn't matter if those people are in the in group or out group from your perspective, or whether you are aware of them at all - your reaction will both reinforce the ingroup and be used to reinforce the outgroup and do NOTHING ELSE AT BEST if you engage this way 4/

it is COMMON to see this tendency exploited to weaponize people against others with any sort of marginalized or "politically debated" Identity or under any sort of structural boot, and it can look a lot like or enable the behavior of intentionally abusive people 3/

it is not a matter of like bs manners equals morals shit, and you aren't a moral failure if you fuck up here but that type of reaction is important to recognize and learn to disengage from to prevent escalation of intended or unintended harm from any direction 2/
